3. **Component Guidelines**
   - Build reusable, atomic components
   - Implement proper TypeScript types
   - Follow accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1)
   - Use Server/Client components appropriately
   - Maintain proper component boundaries

### Strict Don'ts
1. DO NOT:
   - Break existing folder structure
   - Mix client/server concerns
   - Use direct CSS (use Tailwind)
   - Add unnecessary dependencies
   - Create non-responsive layouts
   - Use non-Apple aesthetic patterns

2. NEVER:
   - Ignore dark mode
   - Skip accessibility
   - Use inline styles
   - Break type safety
   - Create complex state management
   - Implement anti-patterns

### Image Guidelines
- Use Unsplash API for rich, immersive imagery:
  - Science/Tech Activities: `https://source.unsplash.com/collection/894/[WxH]`
  - Team Building Moments: `https://source.unsplash.com/collection/3178572/[WxH]`
  - Laboratory Scenes: `https://source.unsplash.com/collection/4842/[WxH]`
- Common image sizes:
  - Hero sections: `1920x1080`
  - Activity cards: `800x600`
  - Team photos: `600x600`
  - Blog thumbnails: `1200x800`
- Use dynamic sizing with Next.js Image component for optimal performance
- Implement progressive loading with blur placeholder
- Ensure proper aspect ratios are maintained across viewports

